## Project
Housing Regulation Compliance Agent — see ARCHITECTURE.md, FEATURES.md, DATA_MODELS.md, PROMPTS.md for full context.

## Stack rules
- Python 3.11, Streamlit multi-page, Supabase, Pydantic v2, anthropic SDK
- Primary LLM: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 via anthropic SDK
- Fallback LLM: openai gpt-4o if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY not set
- Final fallback: rule-based engine in core/compliance/rules.py (no API key needed)

## Architecture rules
- pages/ files: UI only — import from core/ and db/, zero business logic
- core/ files: never import streamlit
- All DB access: db/client.py only — never call supabase directly elsewhere
- All LLM calls: core/llm/client.py only — never import anthropic/openai elsewhere
- Config: config.py using Pydantic Settings — never use os.getenv() directly

## Code quality rules
- Type hints on every function signature
- Pydantic models for all DB row types — never return raw dicts from DB functions
- Never use eval() — always json.loads()
- Never hardcode city, state, or jurisdiction names in logic files
- Jurisdiction resolution always via DB lookup returning jurisdiction_id (int)
- deduplicate_sources() from core/rag/utils.py — never inline dedup logic
- Legal disclaimer always appended from config.LEGAL_DISCLAIMER

## Naming conventions
- DB query functions: get_*, create_*, update_*, delete_* prefix
- Pydantic models: PascalCase matching table name (Regulation, Jurisdiction etc)
- Page functions: show_* prefix for each UI section
- Core functions: snake_case, descriptive verbs

## Testing
- Every core/ module must have a corresponding test in tests/
- Tests must not call Supabase — use dependency injection with mock db client